title: Independent candidate Khalid Khan wins PK-62 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Khalid Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-62 Charsadda-I by securing 29,402 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner up was QWP candidate Sikandar Hayat Khan who bagged 17,310 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 42.63 per cent.
